# CODEOWNERS — the platform-enforced human-review boundary for the autonomous loop
# (council 2026-06-02; docs/adr/0005-autotest-governed-auto-merge.md).
#
# The autotest loop may auto-merge ordinary harness CODE and product fixes on green CI.
# It must NEVER auto-merge a change to the files that GOVERN it — its merge/guard logic,
# the kill switch, the classifier, the safety tripwire, CI policy, the deploy/dependency
# supply-chain, or the governance docs. An in-repo guard (gitops.classify_change +
# tests/test_autonomy_tripwire.py) is NECESSARY but not sufficient, because it is run by
# the same identity that writes the code. THIS file is the real stop: it requires a human
# code-owner review on the constitution set.
#
# REQUIRED operator setup for this to actually bind (do once):
#   1. Settings → Branches → branch protection on `main`: enable "Require a pull request
#      before merging" + "Require review from Code Owners" + "Require status checks to pass".
#   2. Ensure the autotest bot identity (GITHUB_TOKEN / AUTOTEST_GH_PAT) is NOT an admin and
#      does NOT have "bypass branch protections". Then the loop literally cannot merge these
#      paths — only a human code-owner can. (See monitoring/README.md analogue + the ADR.)

